    type='think',
    think='Now I have a good understanding of the codebase. Let me summarize wha
t exists and what needs to be built:\n\n**What exists:**\n- Database schema with
all required tables (users, user_profiles, match_actions, matches, conversations
, conversation_participants, blocks, etc.)\n- Database entities in TypeORM\n- In
itial migration creating all tables\n- Auth module (login, JWT, guards)\n- Profi
le module\n- OpenAPI-generated models for matching in both shared-types and mobi
le\n- Design system with basic tokens, theme, and some atoms/molecules\n- Mobile
app with DI, routing, auth bloc, profile bloc\n- Redis config exists\n\n**What n
eeds to be built:**\n1. **API (NestJS)**:\n   - Matching module (controller, ser
vice, DTOs, module)\n   - Matching controller with:\n     - GET /matching/recomm
endations?mode=&limit=\n     - POST /matching/actions\n   - Matches controller w
ith:\n     - GET /matches?limit=&cursor=\n   - Redis service integration for cac
hing\n   - Socket.io integration for match:created events\n   - ProfileCompletio
nGuard on matching endpoints\n\n2. **Mobile (Flutter)**:\n   - Matching reposito
ry + impl\n   - Matching bloc (event, state, bloc)\n   - Match list cubit (state
, cubit)\n   - Home page with swipe cards\n   - Match list page\n   - Empty reco
mmendation view\n   - Design system components:\n     - SwActionButton\n     - S
wipeCard\n     - SwipeCardStack\n     - MatchSuccessDialog\n     - MatchListItem
\n   - Update DI, routes\n   - Socket.io client integration for match:created\n\
